CATEGORY: OTHER
SERVICE: knowledge
TASK: Spike — retrieval mechanism (corrected after user input)
SYMPTOM: n/a (spike, no production code yet)
ROOT_CAUSE: Chunk-based retrieval (vector or BM25) cannot structurally represent "newsletter X overrides policy Y for date Z" — the LLM must infer the override from unstructured context, which is untestable and fragile for a citation-mandatory system. This root cause was only identifiable after understanding the corpus (school policies + newsletters with date-specific exceptions) and query pattern (multi-hop temporal reasoning).
PREVENTED_BY: In a spike, gather corpus characteristics, query patterns, scale, and ops constraints BEFORE researching or evaluating any option. The spike questions in the service CLAUDE.md are a checklist, not optional. Do not write the spike document until those questions are answered by the user.
SOLUTION: Graphiti with Neo4j Aura Free. See docs/spikes/retrieval.md.
DEAD_ENDS: Pure vector search (structurally mismatched to temporal entity resolution); Pageindex (no access control, paid-only); R2R (collection permissioning unstable); Graphiti-as-MCP for access control (behavioral enforcement, not structural — deferred); post-filter on source_id (access control must be pre-filter).

[2026-03-21]
CATEGORY: CONFIG_BUG
SERVICE: cross-cutting
TASK: Add PreToolUse hook to enforce heuristics.log append-only rule
SYMPTOM: Hook fired silently (no block, no error) when Edit was called on heuristics.log
ROOT_CAUSE: Two compounding issues: (1) Claude Code hooks run with /bin/sh, not bash — <<< here-string syntax is bash-specific and fails silently in sh. (2) Tool input is NOT available as $TOOL_INPUT_* environment variables; it is passed as JSON via stdin to the hook process.
PREVENTED_BY: When writing hooks, always parse stdin JSON with `python3 -c "import sys,json; d=json.load(sys.stdin); ..."` to access tool input. Never use <<< or bash-specific syntax. Test hooks by capturing stdin to a file first before adding logic.
SOLUTION: Rewrote all hooks to use python3 JSON stdin parsing. All pre-existing hooks using <<< were also broken and were fixed in the same pass.
DEAD_ENDS: $TOOL_INPUT_FILE_PATH env var (does not exist); <<< here-string (sh incompatible); grep on env vars (nothing to grep).

