           litellm.success_callback only fires for synchronous litellm.completion calls.
           First attempt used litellm.async_success_callback (no underscore) — this silently
           creates a new dead attribute and does nothing.
PREVENTED_BY: When token tracking shows zeros after the first query, check whether the LLM
             calls are sync or async. If using Agents SDK or any async framework, set BOTH:
               litellm.success_callback = [fn]
               litellm._async_success_callback = [async_fn]
             Test by asserting _usage_log is non-empty after a single dry-run query.
SOLUTION: Added async def _async_capture_usage wrapper; set litellm._async_success_callback.

[2026-04-21]
CATEGORY: ENVIRONMENT
SERVICE: poc/openkb_eval
TASK: OpenKB eval harness — Gemini via Agents SDK
SYMPTOM: UnsupportedParamsError from Gemini: "parallel_tool_calls is not supported"
ROOT_CAUSE: OpenAI Agents SDK passes parallel_tool_calls=False to every LLM call.
           Gemini rejects this parameter as unsupported.
PREVENTED_BY: Set litellm.drop_params = True at module level before any LLM calls when
             using any non-OpenAI model via litellm with the Agents SDK. Without this,
             every agent tool call fails on Gemini.
SOLUTION: litellm.drop_params = True added at the top of eval_harness.py.
