[2026-04-24]
CATEGORY: TOOLING
SERVICE: cross-cutting
TASK: verify deployed service health endpoint
SYMPTOM: `curl` output for a JSON endpoint came back as `{ status: string, version: string }` — unquoted keys, literal "string" values. Looked like an OpenAPI schema. Verbose flag (-sv) showed no HTTP headers either.
ROOT_CAUSE: The rtk hook rewrites `curl` → `rtk curl`, which summarises/filters JSON responses to reduce token count. The filter produces a schema-like summary instead of the raw bytes.
PREVENTED_BY: When you need the raw response from a service (e.g. verifying a version hash, checking an exact field value), always use `rtk proxy curl ...` — the `proxy` subcommand bypasses all filtering and returns the real output.
SOLUTION: Re-ran with `rtk proxy curl` and received correct JSON: `{"status":"healthy","version":"bb2f256..."}`.
