[2026-04-25]
CATEGORY: TOOLING
SERVICE: src/channel_web
TASK: Insert a new JS function before addAnswer in app.js using Python str.replace()
SYMPTOM: The replacement string was written to the file without error, but the new
function body was missing. The call site (addPendingCard) was present but the function
definition was not.
ROOT_CAUSE: Python str.replace() returns the original string silently when the pattern
does not match — no exception, no warning. The anchor comment `// ── Answers ──...` had
a different number of em-dashes in the file than in the replacement string.
PREVENTED_BY: After any Python str.replace() that is supposed to insert or replace
something non-trivial, immediately grep for one unique token from the inserted text.
If not found, the replacement silently failed and must be retried with the corrected
anchor string.
SOLUTION: Used the Edit tool directly with the correct anchor string (read from the file
first), which succeeded immediately.

[2026-04-26]
CATEGORY: RETRIEVAL_BUG
SERVICE: src/knowledge
TASK: UAT of thinking panel — question "How do Montessori materials facilitate the move
      from concrete to abstract learning?" produced a plausible-looking answer despite
      routing selecting 0 nodes.
SYMPTOM: Trace showed "Topics: (0 total)", "Selected 0 chunks", "Sending 0 chunks
         (11582 chars) to LLM", "Answer synthesized (1928 chars)". Answer was coherent
         but hallucinated — sourced from LLM training data, not the corpus.
ROOT_CAUSE: When `section_parts` was empty after node selection, `multi.py` constructed
            `sections_text` as `"(no sections selected)\n\n{routing_outline}"`. The
            synthesis prompt's instruction "Answer using ONLY the sections above" was
            insufficient — the routing outline acted as a plausible knowledge hint and
            the LLM answered from training data rather than refusing.
PREVENTED_BY: Integration test: after a query that routes to 0 nodes, assert the response
              answer matches the canned no-content string exactly. Do not assert only
              that `selected_nodes == []` — verify the answer text too, because the LLM
              may still produce output if any context is passed.
SOLUTION: Short-circuit in `multi.py` before synthesis: if `section_parts` is empty,
          return the canned response directly without any LLM call. The routing outline
          is never passed as synthesis context under any circumstances.
          Fixed in: src/knowledge/indexer/multi.py (2026-04-26). Deployed as revision
          knowledge-00012-4n7.

